title: Sao Tome and Principe Imports
description: Imports in Sao Tome and Principe decreased to 9.89 USD Million in September from 12.22 USD Million in August of 2022. Imports in Sao Tome and Principe averaged 15.19 USD Million from 1999 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 42.28 USD Million in September of 2014 and a record low of 3.23 USD Million in June of 1999. Sao Tome and Principe main imports are: food (22 percent of total imports), capital equipment (21 percent) and fuel (15 percent). Others include: construction materials and beverages. Main import partner is Portugal (54 percent of total imports). Others include: Angola (22 percent), China (5 percent) and Nigeria (2 percent). This page provides - Sao Tome and Principe Imports - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Central Bank of Sao Tome and Principe
